{"author":{"id":"b78c39e7b13f90a5827abfba043255fe7a4ede1499df23f110fffe5abfa44adc"},"ops":[{"type":1,"timestamp":1770048587,"nonce":"ZeNmIMoePTm6MXZDAa69fmoVItY=","metadata":{"github-id":"I_kwDOQ241x87nq12f","github-url":"https://github.com/rolker/ros2_agent_workspace/issues/126","origin":"github"},"title":"Enhancement: Workspace Context Awareness \u0026 Drift Detection","message":"**Problem**\nAgents may check out feature branches that are significantly outdated (drifted from main), leading to confusion when directory structures change (e.g., `workspaces/` vs `layers/` in PR #115). There is no immediate warning that the working context is stale.\n\n**Proposed Solution**\nAdd tools to make context staleness obvious:\n1.  **Quickstart Update**: Add a step to `AI_CLI_QUICKSTART.md` to explicitly check `git log HEAD..main --oneline | wc -l`.\n2.  **Status Tool**: Update `check_full_status.py` or create `get_workspace_state` to report \"Branch Age\" (commits behind main).\n3.  **Warning**: `agent start-task` should warn if the base branch is invalid or significantly behind.\n\n**Acceptance Criteria**\n- [ ] Status tools report commits-behind-main count.\n- [ ] Quickstart checklist includes specific drift-check commands.\n\n---\n**🤖 Authored-By**: `Antigravity Agent`\n**🧠 Model**: `Gemini 3 Pro (High)`","files":null}]}